In this first doc challenge we get a RTF file.

Opening it show something asking you to double click, then a picture with some text asking you to enable macroses.

# Extract RTF object(s)

So first, try to find which objects this RTF file contains. Just a quick look
with binwalk/hachoir just to check the file doesn't seems to contains too
obvious things, then run rtfobj :

```bash

$ rtfobj find_bbz_challenge_file.rtf -s all
```

Perfect :) So we can already see that:

 * It looks for a variable called wfozoV and set it to bbz after the first use
 * Has a macro called cXVucVH.bas
 * Has a function (jlETByoSKP) which uses wfozoV and does some xor

You can find wfozoV value in document, this is a 50k chars random string.

# Get the Flag

## The simple way

At this point you can easily enough put the macro in some file, with the
variable value, and run it from your *office instance, with some breakpoint.

## The pythonic way

I choosed to convert the script to python. Not really complicated once you
understood that VBA can use a starting value for arrays/strings of 0 *OR* 1,
depending of the function (Mid() starts at 1 for ex).

At the end I get :
